  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "If we try to trace a transaction for which we don't have the state any more (e.g. via `debug.traceTransaction(\"0xb44ab4e708611c6cd2125bdedc013e922e876a6e1d45750541f258b14ae57c48\")` on Rinkeby with a recently synced node), Geth returns an error along the lines of `missing trie node 2361beabb6dd28f9d58136dd5648cfdc7336975ca6c86038c799a880d64de65d (path )`. While this is perfectly valid, it may not be the most helpful message to a user. We should catch missing trie node errors in the tracers and convert them into `required historical state unavailable`.",
